If you have dirty it already, you can begin staking the tent to the ground. Doing so will keep the tent taut making it simpler for that fly to become setup. Other than this staking the tent down will give it strength to resist the wind even without additional weight within it. The peg you use to stake the tent ought to be driven in at a 45 degree facing away from the tent.

